The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), has reiterated its unwavering commitment to prioritizing the welfare of the youths in Abia State. This was even as the party also restated that it remained committed to seeing that the youths are given equal opportunities in the party both at the state and local government levels. Hon Alwell Asiforo Okere, the PDP Chairman in Abia State, stated this when he received the delegation of PDP youth leaders across the 17 local government areas of the state at party secretariat in Umuahia, the state capital on Wednesday. He applauded the youth leaders for their invaluable contributions towards the socio-economic growth of the state and for their unwavering support to the PDP-led administration in Abia State and also admonished them to remain calm and to support policies and programmes aimed at promoting unity and peaceful co-existence in the state. According to the former Deputy Speaker of the Abia State House of Assembly, “The youths must shun acts capable of destroying the image of the party in Abia. They should engage in activities aimed at upholding the tenets of the party as the electioneering campaigns begin in earnest.” Earlier in his speech, the leader of the delegation, who also doubled as youth leader of the PDP in Isiala Ngwa South Local Government Area of Abia State, Mr. Donatus Orji, disclosed that they were in the party’s secretariat to felicitate with state PDP chairman on his recent birthday celebration.